        <updateDate>2021-01-19T16:47:30Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>New Markets Stabilization Act</b></p> <p>This bill modifies provisions of the new markets tax credit (NMTC). Specifically, it increases and extends the NMTC limitation through 2022 and allows a carryback of the credit for five years. The bill also exempts the NMTC from the 75% general business credit limitation, revises debt modification rules for NMTC issuers and borrowers, and permanently exempts the NMTC from the alternative minimum tax.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
